					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Registers a gift of land by purchase by <hi rend="bold">Kaṇṇagan Karumāṇikkam</hi> <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> <hi rend="bold">Vaḷava-Vichchādira Pallavaraiyan</hi> for rearing a flower garden after his name, to the god Tiruvaraṅgattāḻvār in Viḷānāḍu, a sub-division of Dīnachintāmaṇivaḷanāḍu. The <hi rend="italic">Śrīkaryam</hi> of the temple was <hi rend="italic">adhikārigaḷ</hi> <hi rend="bold">Bhuvaninārāyaṇa Mūvēndavēḷār.</hi> The record is dated in the <hi rend="bold">39th regnal year</hi> of the king.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
